casebody.data:
Melanie M. (Krull) NIGH, Appellant,
v.
Phillip N. KRULL, Jr., Respondent. WD 81591 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: March 5, 2019 Michael A. Insco, St. Joseph, MO, Attorney for Appellant. Lisa A. Hansen, Lee's Summit, MO, Attorney for Respondent. Before Division Three: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Presiding Judge, and Lisa White Hardwick and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

Ms. Melanie Nigh appeals from the judgment of the Circuit Court of Andrew County, Missouri, which partially modified the existing child custody arrangement between Ms. Nigh and her ex-husband, Mr. Phillip Krull, Jr., following a bench trial. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
